;   ua_fits_close.pro   version 1.0    30 September 1997;*NAME:;	UA_FITS_CLOSE;;*PURPOSE:;	Close a FITS data file;;*CATEGORY:;	INPUT/OUTPUT;;*CALLING SEQUENCE:;	UA_FITS_CLOSE,fcb;;*INPUTS:;	FCB: fits control block returned by UA_FITS_OPEN.;;*KEYWORD PARAMETERS:;       /NO_ABORT: Set to return to calling program instead of a RETALL;               when an I/O error is encountered.  If set, the routine will;               return with !err=-1 and a message in the keyword MESSAGE.;               If not set, UA_FITS_CLOSE will print the message and issue a;               RETALL;       MESSAGE = value: Output error message;	;*EXAMPLES:;	Open a FITS file, read some data, and close it with UA_FITS_CLOSE;;		UA_FITS_OPEN,'infile',fcb;		UA_FITS_READ,fcb,data;		UA_FITS_READ,fcb,moredata;		UA_FITS_CLOSE,fcb;;*HISTORY:;	Written by:	D. Lindler	August, 1995